news.title: OMBR Layout: Court restores acquired land favouring Bengaluru development body
news.para: On March 31, 2016, a single bench held that physical possession of the land in question (about 2.5 acres) was not taken and hence, the acquisition had lapsed and section 24(2) of the new Land Acquisition Act (of 2013) would apply.

news.title: Pune civic body to start survey of STPs in big housing societies
news.para: The administration has given directives to housing complexes to treat sewage on their premises. Societies not operating treatment plants properly will be fined.

news.title: About 20 lakh buildings in Kerala were out of property tax net in 2021
news.para: Local bodies exempted 19.8 lakh residential buildings below 660sq ft from paying property tax in the state, accounting for 13% of total buildings as per the data collected in 2021.

news.title: Housr acquires StayAbode, enters Bengaluru market
news.para: The price point will range from Rs 14,000- 24,000 for twin sharing and Rs 25,000-50,000 for single occupancy in Housr co-living.

news.title: PropShare raises Rs 367 crore from WestBridge Capital & Pravega Ventures
news.para: "By partnering with WestBridge Capital, we plan to grow to over $1 billion in transacted assets on the platform by expanding into newer geographies and property types, while keeping technology and our investors at the core of our offering," said Hashim Khan, CTO, Propshare.

news.title: Now, Chandigarh administration officials to visit Delhi to meet MHA officials
news.para: The UT administration had last converted leasehold plots into freehold in 1983 in commercial category. The matter was also taken by up MP Kirron Kher with the MHA and ministry of urban development (MoUD).

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CRDA to lease out flats built for government employees
news.para: In the first lot, the CRDA has put up the D1 Tower, containing 120 flats, for lease to earn about Rs 8-10 crore per annum.

news.title: Over 15 get land ownership certificates in Noida
news.para: At the ceremony, the DM said that officials have handed out over 16,000 of the over 18,000 documents in the district. The state government aims to hand over 2.5 crore ‘gharauni’ certificates across the state by 2023.

news.title: Law firms go for bigger, smarter office spaces as business grows
news.para: The firms are on the lookout for buildings that offer better connectivity, multifunctional spaces, collaborative environment, good recreational and rest areas that have open spaces, according to property consultants and law firms.

news.title: Upkeep fee high, but no sewage plant, club: BPTP Astaire Garden residents at protest
news.para: A similar protest was staged at another project of the developer — BPTP Spacio — located in Sector 37D. Its residents too complained of poor upkeep and basic amenities.

news.title: Noida: Ajnara Le Garden & Ajnara Homes residents demand completion of five towers
news.para: Residents of Eldeco society in Sector 119 also protested against pending registries. Of the 1,200 residents, the registries of around 200 are pending.

news.title: MahaRERA plans to help kickstart Rs 78,000-crore stalled, lapsed housing projects
news.para: Out of the 36,000 projects registered in the last five years in Maharashtra, 4,500 projects, or around 12%, have lapsed, and the state regulatory body’s new vertical will help solve the issues around these projects.

news.title: No OC, builder diverted funds: Ansal Esencia buyers
news.para: The RWA members said the project, which has around 600 residents and allottees, is still incomplete and without OC and electricity connection.

news.title: Pune: 100 people to get back land in Maan-Mhalunge scheme
news.para: The scheme announced in 2018 has finally picked up momentum with 253 plot owners being given demarcated land in the coming week, officials from Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh gives green signal to CRDA to auction lands in Amaravati
news.para: The government set the off-set price at Rs 10 crore per acre and allowed to auction about 248 acres to pool up Rs 2,480 crore.
